Fizz Le <p><center><img src="http://fizz.i8.com/sig2.gif" border="0" alt="Free Gnome"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=erruinembercore>Erruin Embercore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/5/02 8:38:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Soloing HS entrance - spoiler</span><hr size=1> I started doing this from level 54 onward.<br>
<br>
I do have a rend robe, but was doing HS before I got it, it just lets you kill more targets per cycle.<br>
<br>
Respawn is about 22 minute cycle once you get going.<br>
<br>
When you initially zone into HS, if you do not move at all (dont turn, sit, duck, whatever) you are normally safe from agroing the platform guards. If you wait long enough however, one will eventually path to a point just close enough to notice you, so dont rely on it as a safe spot.<br>
<br>
Aside from the 2 platform guards (which can be goo's, feasters/sperms, or plaguebone, seplechur, or, very rarely, undertaker skeletons), there are 8 golems, 2 in each compass direction.<br>
<br>
When breaking, zone in with Spellshield (or Manasink) and Epic (or Manaskin) up to soak potential HT's. Have some form of levitate up as well, by preference, to be able to bail safely. Resistances are unimportant, use gear that gives you hp and mana.<br>
My spell list when hunting here generally are: Root, Levitation, Solist's or Draught of ice, Tishan's Discord, Atol's, Gate, Harvest, and 1 other spell, usually another DD or stun, but sometimes Fetter for breaking, to get a longer root on the second guard while killing the first one. Stuns are useful to cut down on lifetap attempts from the skells if skins burn off. Another good choice is manaskin or manasink if you dont have the Epic.<br>
<br>
Damage AE's on the platform are generally a bad idea by the way, I've had them pull stuff up from the pit on a number of occassions, and that warp in right on top of you when that happens... not a fun thing, as one will often be an undertaker, and the rest sep's, all with HT's.<br>
<br>
Staggering the kills of the guards is prefered, to let you med and renew skins between repops.<br>
<br>
Once you kill the guards, start pulling golems - start with the ones to the north, then west, then south. Only pull east if you are very confident about fighting an undertaker skeleton, which HT for 800+ and can often summon. Also be wary of the false steps to the east, its a illusion/pit trap that will drop you off the platform if you try to run up it. Depending on what buffs you have on and normal mana effiency, its unlikely that you will kill all the mobs before they start to respawn, unless you have a partner, so you wont need to worry about wanting to pull the east golems anyway.<br>
<br>
You can kite around the track running around the platform, I prefer to root and nuke once snared, as mine tend to stick on these mobs fairly well, even while burning them.<br>
<br>
The pathing is a bit funny on the track, with a discontinuity line running north from the northeast pillar - if you cross it, the mob will generally switch the direction it is chasing you around the platform unless already in melee range, and even sometimes then too. Avoid standing directly in line between the center of the plaform and any of the steps, and stay on the track, or the mob may path through the middle of the platform if directly accross from you, although thats only a minor irritation if you are root-nuking as it wont get very far.<br>
<br>
Golems, Goo's, and Sep skel's are dark blue until 60, and still split half-and-half blue/ light blue even then.<br>
Good experience when quad spots are camped, but a pain to get a rez if you get killed, so I recommend you bail out if you fall below 800 hp, especially if a guard/ HT'er repop is due soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagnetar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magnetar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/7/02 9:47:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=310.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.facelink.com/Baddorly?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing HS entrance - spoiler</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the tips, Erruin. I have a question.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Have some form of levitate up as well, by preference, to be able to bail safely.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So if you get in trouble, you jump into the pit while levitating and gate out on the way down?<br>
